article.headline: Alcorn St. 66, Alabama St. 65
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Delvin Thompson scored 19 points and Alcorn State beat Alabama State 66-65 on Monday night. The Braves (10-16, 9-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference) also got 12 points from Cornell Landry in the win over the Hornets (9-16, 7-7). Alcorn State led 31-26 at halftime after Alabama State hit six field goals and shot 28 percent from the floor in the first half. The Hornets outscored the Braves 39-35 in the second half, but fell short. Moses Edun led Alabama State with 16 points, Andrew Mayles and Miguel Morton added 14 apiece and Richard Lott scored 12 and led all players with nine rebounds.
